Currently, searches on Confluence mobile return only a limited set of results: results where page titles match the query.

It would be helpful if mobile search returned the same results as the full version of Confluence, because people often know what they want to find (e.g. all pages that address "email settings") but they don't usually know the exact page titles. Even if they know the page titles, why force people to run multiple searches to obtain the information that a single search might produce?

