Usually, if a user is part of the 'confluence-administrators' group, they are considered as 'super users', which have full administrative access to Confluence, and can see all the content.

However, certain macros, for example the 'Content Report Table' and 'Activity Stream' does not respect these permissions, and will not show any results as long as the user does not have the 'View Space' space permission.

This is kind of a contradiction, as the 'super users' are supposed to be able to view all content, and can therefore cause confusion.

