Raising this on behalf of a customer from a support request.

In a similar vein to CONF-28831, it would be nice if there were an option for link suggestions to return results for the current space only. The use case here is if there are many spaces with the same page name, and the user has no desire to create links across spaces. The same logic should apply for any functionality that uses a page selector, e.g. an Include Page Macro.

This would be especially helpful to customers who use Confluence for documentation and have a different spaces for different versions, with a lot of the same page names across spaces (not unlike our own confluence.atlassian.com).

