The Popular Labels macro shows all labels that are used, regardless of whether or not the user has permissions to view the pages that uses the label. 

This could cause some problems, especially when organizations have private labels that are used only for certain pages/spaces, and the labels can still be seen by users that do not have the permission to view the pages within.

Hence, it would be helpful if the macro would not show labels that the users does not have permission to view its contents

